# ZMK Keymap Guidance

Apply this rule when editing `config/*.keymap`.

## Common Behaviors

- `&kp KEY`: press a keycode.
- `&mt HOLD TAP`: mod-tap behavior, hold for modifier and tap for key.
- `&lt LAYER KEY`: layer-tap behavior, hold for layer and tap for key.
- `&mo LAYER`: momentarily activate a layer while held.
- `&to LAYER`: switch to a layer.
- `&trans`: transparent key, falling through to lower layers.
- `&none`: disabled key.
- `&mkp BUTTON`: mouse button behavior.

## Local Conventions

- Do not automatically rename existing numbered layers such as `layer_6`.
- Keep new layer names meaningful when adding new layers.
- Keep combos under `/ { combos { ... }; };`.
- Keep macros under `/ { macros { ... }; };`.
- Keep custom behaviors under `/ { behaviors { ... }; };`.
- Check keymap-drawer output when a visible key changes.
- Do not infer side hardware placement from Kconfig flag names.

## roBa Specific Notes

- `roBa_R` is the physical trackball / PMW3610 / SPI side.
- `roBa_L` is the physical encoder side.
- `CONFIG_EC11` and `CONFIG_ZMK_POINTING` may intentionally exist in both side `.conf` files.
- Visible keymap changes should update `keymap-drawer/roBa.yaml` and regenerate `keymap-drawer/roBa.svg`.
